HEADWORD: Bill holder
<hw>Bill" hold`er</hw> <pr>(b⟦icr⟧l" h⟦omac⟧l`d⟦etil⟧r)</pr>.
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A person who holds a bill or acceptance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A device by means of which bills, etc., are
held.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Billhook</ent>⟦br⟧
